---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Agent Party Planner | The Compendium">
  <main class="relative min-h-screen overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Decorative Background Element -->
    <div
      class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-full max-w-6xl aspect-square bg-gold-600/5 blur-[120px] rounded-full -z-10"
    >
    </div>

    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20 relative">
      <!-- Navigation -->
      <nav class="flex justify-between items-center mb-16">
        <a href="/" class="flex items-center gap-2 group">
          <div
            class="w-8 h-8 bg-crimson rounded rotate-45 flex items-center justify-center border border-gold-600/30 group-hover:bg-red-800 transition-colors"
          >
            <span class="text-white font-bold -rotate-45">A</span>
          </div>
          <span
            class="font-bold tracking-wider text-parchment uppercase text-sm group-hover:text-gold-400 transition-colors"
            >Agent Party Planner</span
          >
        </a>
        <div class="hidden md:flex gap-8 text-sm font-medium text-slate-400">
          <a href="/#the-party" class="hover:text-gold-400 transition-colors"
            >The Party</a
          >
          <a href="/compendium" class="text-gold-400 transition-colors"
            >Compendium</a
          >
        </div>
      </nav>

      <!-- Content -->
      <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gold max-w-none">
        <h1
          class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-parchment mb-8 tracking-wide uppercase"
        >
          The Compendium
        </h1>

        <p class="text-xl text-slate-300 mb-12 leading-relaxed">
          The <strong>Agent Party Planner</strong> is an interactive web tool that
          lets you visually configure and export <em>Agent Orchestration</em> packages.
          Using a Dungeons &amp; Dragons theme, you can assemble a "Party" of specialized
          AI agents, customize their personalities, and download a ready-to-use orchestration
          setup tailored for platforms like Gemini or Claude. All entirely in your
          browser.
        </p>

        <h2
          class="text-2xl font-bold text-gold-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider border-b border-tavern-800 pb-2"
        >
          The Multi-Tier Architecture
        </h2>
        <p class="text-slate-300 mb-6">
          The exported packages follow a strict 3-tier hierarchy that separates
          meta-planning from actual coding. This ensures privacy, reduces
          clutter in your target codebase, and maintains clear roles.
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-8 mb-16">
          <section
            class="bg-tavern-900/50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-tavern-800"
          >
            <h3
              class="text-xl font-bold text-parchment mb-3 flex items-center gap-3"
            >
              <span class="text-gold-500">I.</span> The War Room <span
                class="text-sm font-normal text-slate-400 tracking-widest uppercase"
                >(Meta-Level)</span
              >
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">
              The strategic layer where you interact with meta-agents to define
              the quest, set constraints, and adjust rules mid-flight. It runs
              in an isolated directory to keep your main codebase clean.
            </p>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-slate-400 mt-4 space-y-2">
              <li>
                <strong class="text-slate-300">The Game Creator:</strong> The architect
                and your primary brainstorming partner.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-slate-300">The Master of Spies:</strong> The real-time
                analyst, critiquing orchestration inefficiencies.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-slate-300">The Bard:</strong> The chronicler who
                translates technical achievements into an engaging narrative recap.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section
            class="bg-tavern-900/50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-tavern-800"
          >
            <h3
              class="text-xl font-bold text-parchment mb-3 flex items-center gap-3"
            >
              <span class="text-gold-500">II.</span> The GM Session <span
                class="text-sm font-normal text-slate-400 tracking-widest uppercase"
                >(Coordinator)</span
              >
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300">
              The Game Master (GM) runs inside the actual codebase. It acts as
              the project manager&mdash;reading journals, evaluating results,
              and spawning the correct Party Members to do the work. The GM
              coordinates but <em>never</em> writes code or runs tests itself.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section
            class="bg-tavern-900/50 p-6 rounded-lg border border-tavern-800"
          >
            <h3
              class="text-xl font-bold text-parchment mb-3 flex items-center gap-3"
            >
              <span class="text-gold-500">III.</span> The Party <span
                class="text-sm font-normal text-slate-400 tracking-widest uppercase"
                >(Sub-Agents)</span
              >
            </h3>
            <p class="text-slate-300 mb-4">
              The specialized workers executing the tasks. The magic lies in
              their <strong>constructive tension</strong>: they are not yes-men,
              but experts who push back on bad plans and scrutinize each other's
              work.
            </p>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
              <div
                class="bg-slate-900/50 p-4 rounded border border-slate-800/50"
              >
                <strong class="text-emerald-400 block mb-1"
                  >🏹 Ranger (Telemetry)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-slate-400"
                  >Data gatherer. No ego, just numbers.</span
                >
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-slate-900/50 p-4 rounded border border-slate-800/50"
              >
                <strong class="text-purple-400 block mb-1"
                  >🧙‍♂️ Wizard (Strategist)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-slate-400"
                  >Creates ambitious attack plans.</span
                >
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-slate-900/50 p-4 rounded border border-slate-800/50"
              >
                <strong class="text-red-400 block mb-1"
                  >⚔️ Warrior (Implementation)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-slate-400"
                  >Pragmatic shipper. Writes the code.</span
                >
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-slate-900/50 p-4 rounded border border-slate-800/50"
              >
                <strong class="text-indigo-400 block mb-1"
                  >🧛‍♂️ Warlock (Code Review)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-slate-400"
                  >Adversarial critic. Blocks bad code.</span
                >
              </div>
              <div
                class="bg-slate-900/50 p-4 rounded border border-slate-800/50 md:col-span-2"
              >
                <strong class="text-cyan-400 block mb-1"
                  >🧑‍⚕️ Healer (Diagnostics)</strong
                >
                <span class="text-slate-400"
                  >Systematic fixer and environment recovery.</span
                >
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>
        </div>
      </article>

      <div class="mt-16 text-center">
        <a
          href="/"
          class="inline-block px-8 py-3 bg-gold-600 hover:bg-gold-500 text-slate-950 font-bold rounded shadow-lg shadow-gold-900/20 transition-all uppercase tracking-wider text-sm"
        >
          Assemble Your Party
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <footer
      class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12 border-t border-tavern-800 flex flex-col md:flex-row justify-between items-center gap-6 text-slate-500 text-xs uppercase tracking-widest"
    >
      <span>© 2026 Agent Party Planner</span>
      <div class="flex gap-8">
        <span>Powered by Bun & Astro</span>
        <a
          href="https://github.com/kelset/agent-party-planner"
          class="hover:text-gold-400">GitHub</a
        >
      </div>
    </footer>
  </main>
</Layout>
